name: Sagartia Erinaceum
description:
--Fig.17--
Sagartia Erinaceum is a creature from Pipitea, an exoplanet located 173 light years from Earth, orbiting the start Poerava.
The species presents itself in huge smack of individuals, reaching millions, flying through harsh storms of Silicon or swimming in cold seas of liquid Cobalt.
Sagartia shells protect both bluehearts located under it, while they also have agile claws to repel predators. Their nervous systems are located in both arm-like structures, which they can use to create a huge net of information through all the inidividuals of the flock.
